-- Treasury's Geithner applauds Senate Bernanke vote
-- 
-- Thu Jan 28, 2010 4:24pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/01/28/us-fed-bernanke-geithner-idUSTRE60R6YT20100128

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - Treasury Secretary Timothy Geithner said on Thursday the Senate "did the right thing" in confirming Federal Reserve Chairman Ben Bernanke for a second term. 

 "The Senate did the right thing," Geithner said in a statement. "Chairman Bernanke will continue to play a vitally important role in guiding the nation's economy." The Senate confirmed Bernanke for a second term on a 70-30 vote on Thursday. (Reporting by  David Lawder ; Editing by Dan Grebler)